label.value: Bone Cancer pM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Bone cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ann Arbor Stage III B-Cell Non-Hodgkin Lymphoma

value.value: Ann Arbor Classification: Stage III: Involvement of lymph node regions on both sides of the diaphragm (III), which also may be accompanied by extralymphatic extension in association with adjacent lymph node involvement (IIIE) or by involvement of the spleen (IIIS) or both (IIIE,S).

label.value: Semi-conscious

value.value: A level of awareness that can be described as varied and intermittent periods of consciousness and unconsciousness.

label.value: Bone Cancer pM1a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Bone cancer with metastasis to lung. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Bone Cancer pM1b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Bone cancer with metastasis to other distant sites. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Bone Cancer Clinical TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of bone cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  The clinical staging includes all relevant data prior to primary definitive therapy, including physical examination, imaging, and biopsy.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Bone Cancer Clinical Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of bone cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Bone Cancer cM0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Bone cancer without evidence of distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Bone Cancer cM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Bone cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Bone Cancer cM1a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Bone cancer with metastasis to lung. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Bone Cancer cM1b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Bone cancer with metastasis to other distant sites. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Soft Tissue Sarcoma TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of soft tissue sarcoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  Kaposi sarcoma, fibromatosis (desmoid tumor), and sarcoma arising from the dura mater, brain, parenchymatous organs, or hollow viscera are not included in this classification. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ann Arbor Stage IV B-Cell Non-Hodgkin Lymphoma

value.value: Ann Arbor Classification: Stage IV: Diffuse or disseminated involvement of one or more extralymphatic organs, with or without associated lymph node involvement; or isolated extralymphatic organ involvement in the absence of adjacent regional lymph node involvement, but in conjunction with disease in distant site(s); or any involvement of the liver or bone marrow, lungs (other than by direct extension from another site), or cerebrospinal fluid.

label.value: Soft Tissue Sarcoma Pathologic TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of soft tissue sarcoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.

label.value: Soft Tissue Sarcoma Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of soft tissue sarcoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Soft Tissue Sarcoma pTX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Soft tissue sarcoma in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Soft Tissue Sarcoma pT0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Soft tissue sarcoma with no evidence of primary tumor. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Soft Tissue Sarcoma pT1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Soft tissue sarcoma with tumor measuring 5 cm or less in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Soft Tissue Sarcoma pT1a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Soft tissue sarcoma with superficial tumor measuring 5 cm or less in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Soft Tissue Sarcoma pT1b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Soft tissue sarcoma with deep tumor measuring 5 cm or less in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Soft Tissue Sarcoma pT2 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Soft tissue sarcoma with tumor measuring more than 5 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Soft Tissue Sarcoma pT2a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Soft tissue sarcoma with superficial tumor measuring more than 5 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Soft Tissue Sarcoma pT2b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Soft tissue sarcoma with deep tumor measuring more than 5 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Refractory Small Lymphocytic Lymphoma

value.value: B-cell small lymphocytic lymphoma that is resistant to treatment.

label.value: Soft Tissue Sarcoma Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of soft tissue sarcoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Soft Tissue Sarcoma pNX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Soft tissue sarcoma in which regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Soft Tissue Sarcoma pN0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Soft tissue sarcoma without regional lymph node metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Soft Tissue Sarcoma pN1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Soft tissue sarcoma with regional lymph node metastasis.  Note: Presence of positive nodes (N1) in M0 tumors is considered Stage III. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Soft Tissue Sarcoma Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of soft tissue sarcoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.  There is no pathologic M0 for soft tissue sarcoma.

label.value: Soft Tissue Sarcoma pM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Soft tissue sarcoma with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Soft Tissue Sarcoma Clinical TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of soft tissue sarcoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.

label.value: Soft Tissue Sarcoma Clinical Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of soft tissue sarcoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Soft Tissue Sarcoma cM0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Soft tissue sarcoma without evidence of distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Soft Tissue Sarcoma cM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Soft tissue sarcoma with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Refractory Burkitt Lymphoma

value.value: Burkitt lymphoma that is resistant to treatment.

label.value: Ligand-Independent Ion Channel Activation

value.value: A process that involves interactions between an intrinsic membrane molecule and an electrochemical gradient across a membrane, often a voltage or a pH gradient. Such interactions may activate or deactivate an ion channel in the membrane, and constitute the basis of nerve conduction of impulse.

label.value: Skin Carcinoma TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of skin carcinoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  It applies to skin squamous cell carcinoma, Merkel cell carcinoma, and other nonmelanoma skin carcinomas. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Skin Squamous Cell Carcinoma or Other Skin Carcinomas TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of skin squamous cell carcinoma or other nonmelanoma skin carcinomas excluding Merkel cell carcinoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Skin Squamous Cell Carcinoma or Other Skin Carcinomas Pathologic TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of skin squamous cell carcinoma or other skin carcinomas excluding Merkel cell carcinoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system. TNM pathologic findings are based on histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Skin Squamous Cell Carcinoma or Other Skin Carcinomas Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of skin squamous cell carcinoma or other skin carcinomas, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.  It excludes cutaneous squamous cell carcinoma of the eyelid and Merkel cell carcinoma.  The TNM pathologic and clinical primary tumor classifications of skin squamous cell carcinoma or other skin carcinomas are the same. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Skin Squamous Cell Carcinoma or Other Skin Carcinomas pTX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Skin squamous cell carcinoma or other skin carcinomas in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Skin Squamous Cell Carcinoma or Other Skin Carcinomas pT0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Skin squamous cell carcinoma or other skin carcinomas with no evidence of primary tumor. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Skin Squamous Cell Carcinoma or Other Skin Carcinomas pTis TNM Finding v7

value.value: Skin squamous cell carcinoma or other skin carcinomas with a finding of carcinoma in situ. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Skin Squamous Cell Carcinoma or Other Skin Carcinomas pT1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Skin squamous cell carcinoma or other skin carcinomas with a tumor size 2 cm or less in greatest dimension with less than two high-risk features.  High-risk features for the primary tumor staging are defined as follows: depth/invasion of more than 2 mm thickness; Clark level equal to or greater than IV; and perineural invasion.  Anatomic location: primary site ear and primary site non-hair-bearing lip.  Differentiation: poorly differentiated or undifferentiated. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Skin Squamous Cell Carcinoma or Other Skin Carcinomas pT2 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Skin squamous cell carcinoma or other skin carcinomas with a tumor size greater than 2 cm in greatest dimension or tumor of any size with two or more high-risk features.  High-risk features for the primary tumor staging are defined as follows: depth/invasion of more than 2 mm thickness; Clark level equal to or greater than IV; and perineural invasion.  Anatomic location: primary site ear and primary site non-hair-bearing lip.  Differentiation: poorly differentiated or undifferentiated. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ann Arbor Stage I Burkitt Lymphoma

value.value: Ann Arbor Classification: Stage I: Involvement of a single lymph node region (I); or localized involvement of a single extralymphatic organ or site in the absence of any lymph node involvement (IE).

label.value: Skin Squamous Cell Carcinoma or Other Skin Carcinomas pT3 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Skin squamous cell carcinoma or other skin carcinomas with tumor invasion of maxilla, mandible, orbit, or temporal bone. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Skin Squamous Cell Carcinoma or Other Skin Carcinomas pT4 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Skin squamous cell carcinoma or other skin carcinomas with tumor invasion of skeleton (axial or appendicular) or perineural invasion of skull base. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Skin Squamous Cell Carcinoma or Other Skin Carcinomas Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of skin squamous cell carcinoma or other skin carcinomas, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.  The TNM pathologic and clinical regional lymph nodes classifications of skin squamous cell carcinoma or other skin carcinomas are the same. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Skin Squamous Cell Carcinoma or Other Skin Carcinomas pNX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Skin squamous cell carcinoma or other skin carcinomas in which regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)
